    "IntroductionArtificial Intelligence (AI) is widely recognized as a significant disruptive force across all domains it touches.",
    "The widespread adoption of AI has experienced significant growth, resulting in a substantial impact on society, potentially with both positive and negative consequences.",
    "While AI applications they develop, there is a need for more practical tools [4,5].",
    "Tools that go beyond checklists or toolkits that can pinpoint sources of potentially ethical issues at any stage of the Data Science lifecycle, preferably before they have an actual impact.",
    "Without such an objective approach, we regard it as very difficult if not impossible to argue transparently about the level of ethical compliance or alignment of a given system or to point out ethical issues so that they can be promptly addressed.One first challenge thus concerns the choice of ethical principles to be considered in order to create AI systems that are ethically aligned and cause no harm to society."
